00:17:11.110 --> 00:17:12.000
The boss?

00:17:12.350 --> 00:17:13.190
Mr. Bei.

00:17:13.720 --> 00:17:14.560
Set it down inside.

00:17:15.550 --> 00:17:16.750
- Hello.
- Hi.

00:17:16.750 --> 00:17:17.590
I'm the owner.

00:17:18.030 --> 00:17:19.310
How can I help you?

00:17:19.590 --> 00:17:20.430
Sir,

00:17:20.960 --> 00:17:23.510
could you recommend some handbags for me?

00:17:25.110 --> 00:17:25.950
They're for gifts.

00:17:26.200 --> 00:17:27.110
No problem.

00:17:27.350 --> 00:17:28.720
I should tell you, though.

00:17:29.070 --> 00:17:30.000
We mainly do

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:31.790
appraisals and maintenance.

00:17:32.110 --> 00:17:33.720
We don't sell new ones, only pre-owned.

00:17:33.960 --> 00:17:35.310
Since they're gifts,

00:17:35.480 --> 00:17:37.030
are you okay with that?

00:17:38.200 --> 00:17:40.000
That's fine, totally fine.

00:17:40.160 --> 00:17:41.200
Let me show you around then.

00:17:41.480 --> 00:17:42.400
This way, please.

00:17:43.400 --> 00:17:44.880
We have many different styles.

00:17:45.480 --> 00:17:46.320
Also,

00:17:46.830 --> 00:17:49.070
could you tell me a bit about her preferences?

00:17:49.240 --> 00:17:50.200
The lady you're

00:17:50.200 --> 00:17:51.880
buying the gift for-

00:17:52.070 --> 00:17:53.750
how old is she?

00:17:54.110 --> 00:17:54.950
Sir,

00:17:55.830 --> 00:17:57.310
you deal with many female customers.

00:17:58.440 --> 00:17:59.640
You must know them best.

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:02.000
Not exactly.

00:18:02.440 --> 00:18:03.750
But I do know handbags.

00:18:04.350 --> 00:18:06.110
So, for this lady,

00:18:06.110 --> 00:18:06.960
about how old is she?

00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:08.830
Any favorite brand, or maybe...

00:18:08.830 --> 00:18:09.790
No need for all that.

00:18:10.070 --> 00:18:11.270
Just a handbag

00:18:11.750 --> 00:18:12.880
that looks simple,

00:18:13.030 --> 00:18:15.070
pretty and goes with everything.

00:18:15.510 --> 00:18:16.790
The kind all girls like.

00:18:17.160 --> 00:18:18.270
Goes with everything?

00:18:20.200 --> 00:18:21.400
Then maybe...

00:18:23.240 --> 00:18:24.080
This one.

00:18:24.920 --> 00:18:25.790
It's a classic design.

00:18:26.550 --> 00:18:28.310
It never goes out of fashion and..

00:18:28.960 --> 00:18:29.800
It holds its value.

00:18:30.510 --> 00:18:31.680
How much is it?

00:18:32.310 --> 00:18:34.350
Under twenty thousand yuan.

00:18:34.830 --> 00:18:35.920
That's pricey.

00:18:36.750 --> 00:18:38.960
Do you have ones that look real

00:18:39.480 --> 00:18:40.510
but are cheaper?

00:18:41.160 --> 00:18:42.070
I could buy several

00:18:42.070 --> 00:18:43.400
to give to a few different girls.

00:18:44.480 --> 00:18:45.480
I'm sorry, sir.

00:18:45.480 --> 00:18:46.880
We only sell authentic items here.

00:18:47.110 --> 00:18:48.400
No knock-offs.

00:18:49.310 --> 00:18:51.070
Why don't you sleep on it?

00:18:54.480 --> 00:18:55.320
Xi,

00:18:56.720 --> 00:18:58.270
what wish did you make?

00:18:59.400 --> 00:19:00.790
It's a secret.

00:19:03.240 --> 00:19:06.790
I'll trade a gift for your secret.

00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:07.840
How's that sound?

00:19:29.860 --> 00:19:30.900
(Bei)

00:19:39.350 --> 00:19:40.350
You should answer that.

00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:42.160
It might be urgent.

00:19:44.340 --> 00:19:45.340
(Bei)

00:19:49.590 --> 00:19:50.430
Hello?

00:19:51.880 --> 00:19:53.070
Sorry, I didn't hear it.

00:19:54.270 --> 00:19:56.550
What? My dad went to see you?

00:19:58.920 --> 00:19:59.760
Okay, okay.

00:20:00.720 --> 00:20:01.750
Alright, see you later.

00:20:05.750 --> 00:20:06.590
Are you okay?

00:20:10.310 --> 00:20:11.440
How did you feel just now?

00:20:14.790 --> 00:20:16.510
I think I remembered something.

00:20:18.510 --> 00:20:19.440
From when I was a kid.

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:21.640
I'm not sure though.

00:20:22.640 --> 00:20:23.480
That's a shame.

00:20:24.240 --> 00:20:25.080
It's my fault.

00:20:25.270 --> 00:20:27.350
I forgot to remind you to silence your phone.

00:20:28.750 --> 00:20:29.720
Do you want to keep going?

00:20:31.720 --> 00:20:33.510
I have to go. Something's come up.

00:20:34.880 --> 00:20:35.880
Can we pick this up tomorrow?

00:20:37.030 --> 00:20:37.870
Sure.

00:20:38.270 --> 00:20:39.440
I can tell

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:41.960
that thing means a lot to you.

00:20:42.680 --> 00:20:43.960
I really hope I can help.

00:20:44.510 --> 00:20:45.440
I'll see you here tomorrow.

00:20:46.030 --> 00:20:46.870
Okay.

00:20:55.200 --> 00:20:56.070
Spicy blood curd.

00:20:58.590 --> 00:20:59.920
Blanched choy sum.

00:21:02.480 --> 00:21:04.590
Quick-fried double crunchy.

00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:08.880
Would you like to order, Mr. Li?

00:21:08.880 --> 00:21:10.480
No, we don't want to go overboard.

00:21:11.510 --> 00:21:12.350
Should we...

00:21:13.070 --> 00:21:13.910
Have a drink?

00:21:14.310 --> 00:21:15.270
No, I'm good.

00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:16.870
No drinking.

00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:18.760
Okay, that'll be all.

00:21:18.840 --> 00:21:19.680
Thanks.

00:21:19.680 --> 00:21:20.520
Sure.

00:21:27.400 --> 00:21:28.240
Here.

00:21:28.510 --> 00:21:29.760
- Have some water.
- Thanks.

00:21:31.000 --> 00:21:31.840
Dad,

00:21:32.310 --> 00:21:33.160
why didn't you call me

00:21:33.160 --> 00:21:34.640
before you came?

00:21:34.640 --> 00:21:35.920
I could've picked you up.

00:21:36.070 --> 00:21:37.440
Pick me up? No need.

00:21:37.640 --> 00:21:39.200
I'm not a three years old.

00:21:39.350 --> 00:21:40.440
Do you think I'd get lost?

00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:43.200
You do your things. Don't mind me.

00:21:43.200 --> 00:21:44.440
If I hadn't asked you,

00:21:44.440 --> 00:21:45.400
were you planning

00:21:45.400 --> 00:21:46.830
to head back once you were done?

00:21:47.030 --> 00:21:48.110
What are you talking about?

00:21:48.480 --> 00:21:50.110
Of course I'd come to see you.

00:22:03.830 --> 00:22:04.720
Well, Mr. Li.

00:22:05.070 --> 00:22:06.000
Do you

00:22:06.200 --> 00:22:07.040
watch games?

00:22:07.350 --> 00:22:08.750
What games?

00:22:09.400 --> 00:22:10.240
Football.

00:22:11.000 --> 00:22:11.840
Oh, football.

00:22:12.200 --> 00:22:14.160
If it's on Channel Five,

00:22:14.310 --> 00:22:15.350
I'll catch it sometimes.

00:22:16.350 --> 00:22:18.830
Do you prefer
the Premier League, the Bundesliga,

00:22:19.000 --> 00:22:19.840
or Serie A?

00:22:20.270 --> 00:22:21.110
Well...

00:22:21.270 --> 00:22:22.640
I like the Premier League.

00:22:22.790 --> 00:22:23.720
Because I think

00:22:24.030 --> 00:22:25.160
they play very elegantly.

00:22:25.160 --> 00:22:26.070
And the pace's fast.

00:22:27.160 --> 00:22:28.310
For Manchester City,

00:22:28.640 --> 00:22:29.960
I bet Haaland will be

00:22:29.960 --> 00:22:31.550
the next Ronaldo.

00:22:33.350 --> 00:22:34.880
You mean that player…

00:22:35.160 --> 00:22:36.000
Cristiano Ronaldo?

00:22:36.240 --> 00:22:37.080
Yeah, Ronaldo.

00:22:37.240 --> 00:22:38.110
I know him.

00:22:38.480 --> 00:22:39.510
He was in the World Cup.

00:22:39.510 --> 00:22:40.350
Exactly.

00:22:40.350 --> 00:22:41.270
- Yes.
- He's brilliant.

00:22:54.310 --> 00:22:55.750
By the way, Mr. Li.

00:22:56.350 --> 00:22:57.200
Do you buy stocks?

00:22:58.310 --> 00:22:59.830
I have some mutual funds.

00:23:00.680 --> 00:23:02.830
That's smart. They're much easier to manage.

00:23:03.480 --> 00:23:05.160
Just put some spare cash in.

00:23:05.480 --> 00:23:06.720
It might grow several times over.

00:23:08.030 --> 00:23:09.160
You see?

00:23:09.160 --> 00:23:10.350
Buffett's held shares

00:23:10.350 --> 00:23:11.720
in a razor company for years.

00:23:12.070 --> 00:23:13.240
He made a fortune from it.

00:23:15.640 --> 00:23:17.270
I still use a manual razor.

00:23:17.270 --> 00:23:18.270
How about you?

00:23:18.790 --> 00:23:19.680
I...

00:23:21.110 --> 00:23:22.510
I use, um…

00:23:23.400 --> 00:23:24.310
An electric one.

00:23:25.110 --> 00:23:26.200
Look at you, all fancy.

00:23:26.720 --> 00:23:27.750
You flatter me.

00:23:28.750 --> 00:23:29.590
Dig in.

00:23:30.030 --> 00:23:30.870
Dig in, Mr. Li.

00:23:31.350 --> 00:23:32.200
Try this.

00:23:32.200 --> 00:23:33.040
Alright.

00:23:33.440 --> 00:23:34.960
Here, have some shrimp.

00:23:34.960 --> 00:23:35.800
Sure.

00:23:41.590 --> 00:23:42.480
Young man,

00:23:44.110 --> 00:23:45.480
your last name is "Bei",

00:23:46.350 --> 00:23:47.960
"B-E-I", right?

00:23:48.200 --> 00:23:49.750
Yes, that's right.

00:23:50.270 --> 00:23:51.270
I wanted to ask,

00:23:51.960 --> 00:23:53.880
what do your parents do?

00:23:54.920 --> 00:23:57.110
They run a small business abroad.

00:23:57.830 --> 00:23:59.000
But they divorced

00:23:59.000 --> 00:23:59.880
when I was very young.

00:24:00.720 --> 00:24:03.030
I grew up with my grandparents.

00:24:08.720 --> 00:24:10.550
Maybe because of that,

00:24:11.070 --> 00:24:13.070
I've always wanted to settle down

00:24:13.070 --> 00:24:14.550
earlier than most people my age.

00:24:16.030 --> 00:24:17.160
When my grandma passed away,

00:24:17.160 --> 00:24:18.350
I realized how important

00:24:18.480 --> 00:24:19.350
it is to cherish

00:24:19.350 --> 00:24:20.440
the people I love.

00:24:26.070 --> 00:24:27.110
Even though

00:24:27.590 --> 00:24:29.000
I didn't have a complete childhood,

00:24:29.350 --> 00:24:30.190
Grandma taught me

00:24:30.680 --> 00:24:32.590
how to love someone wholeheartedly.

00:24:33.790 --> 00:24:34.720
So please, rest assured.

00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:36.350
If you trust me with Xiaoxi,

00:24:36.590 --> 00:24:37.920
I will cherish her with all my heart.

00:24:38.160 --> 00:24:39.110
I'll always love her

00:24:39.310 --> 00:24:40.550
and give her a complete home.

00:24:45.680 --> 00:24:46.520
Oh right.

00:24:53.270 --> 00:24:54.110
Dad.

00:24:55.000 --> 00:24:56.790
- Why did you take out your tools?
- This one…

00:24:57.920 --> 00:24:59.110
I carry them with me.

00:24:59.480 --> 00:25:00.320
Take a look.

00:25:00.480 --> 00:25:01.350
You know what they are?

00:25:05.720 --> 00:25:06.560
They are…

00:25:07.960 --> 00:25:08.800
Two tigers.

00:25:09.240 --> 00:25:10.680
Come on!

00:25:11.200 --> 00:25:12.040
This one

00:25:12.200 --> 00:25:13.040
is a dragon.

00:25:13.510 --> 00:25:14.960
And this one is a phoenix.

00:25:15.400 --> 00:25:16.720
They bring auspiciousness.

00:25:17.920 --> 00:25:19.000
I haven't finished yet.

00:25:20.160 --> 00:25:21.240
I can tell.

00:25:21.750 --> 00:25:23.590
I'll finish carving them soon

00:25:23.960 --> 00:25:26.350
and give them to you when you get married.

00:25:27.240 --> 00:25:28.240
They bring auspiciousness.

00:25:28.240 --> 00:25:29.160
Great.

00:25:29.160 --> 00:25:30.070
Thanks, Mr. Li.

00:25:34.310 --> 00:25:35.310
What is it?

00:25:35.790 --> 00:25:37.200
Two tigers?

00:25:37.720 --> 00:25:38.960
What about it?

00:25:39.680 --> 00:25:40.960
If you hadn't said anything,

00:25:40.960 --> 00:25:42.550
I wouldn't have had a clue what they were.

00:25:42.550 --> 00:25:44.030
I had to say something nice.

00:25:44.240 --> 00:25:45.200
What else could I do?

00:25:45.830 --> 00:25:46.830
You're hilarious.

00:25:46.830 --> 00:25:47.920
Never seen you like this.

00:25:47.980 --> 00:25:48.830
Talking about Ronaldo

00:25:48.830 --> 00:25:50.240
and Warren Buffett.

00:25:51.030 --> 00:25:52.270
You poor thing.

00:25:52.480 --> 00:25:53.960
It was my first time meeting your dad.

00:25:53.960 --> 00:25:55.240
Gotta make a good impression.

00:25:56.240 --> 00:25:57.550
Can't wait to marry me, can you?

00:25:58.640 --> 00:25:59.480
What do you think?

00:25:59.830 --> 00:26:00.670
I have no idea.

00:26:01.270 --> 00:26:02.440
You dare say you don't know?

00:26:02.440 --> 00:26:03.640
How could you not know?

00:26:04.350 --> 00:26:07.270
Fine. I'm closing the shop early tomorrow

00:26:07.270 --> 00:26:08.110
to pick you up.

00:26:08.240 --> 00:26:09.350
Then you'll know for sure.

00:26:09.880 --> 00:26:10.750
For what?

00:26:11.000 --> 00:26:11.840
For what?

00:26:14.750 --> 00:26:15.720
Let's go get married.

00:26:25.720 --> 00:26:26.640
I'll take it as a yes.

00:26:30.880 --> 00:26:31.720
But today,

00:26:31.720 --> 00:26:33.200
I actually hit it off

00:26:34.310 --> 00:26:35.680
with your father.

00:26:56.740 --> 00:26:57.620
(Divorce Agreement)

00:27:45.240 --> 00:27:46.400
Take a look at the agreement.

00:27:47.110 --> 00:27:48.440
Everything is up for discussion.

00:27:49.590 --> 00:27:50.640
No rush to get it done today.

00:27:52.110 --> 00:27:52.950
Why not?

00:27:53.790 --> 00:27:54.630
New regulations.

00:27:55.240 --> 00:27:56.640
There's a 30-day cooling-off period.

00:27:57.110 --> 00:27:57.950
Today...

00:27:59.590 --> 00:28:00.830
we're just filing the application.

00:28:10.830 --> 00:28:12.070
Keep the new car.

00:28:12.790 --> 00:28:14.070
You've signed with an agency.

00:28:14.070 --> 00:28:15.270
You might have shows coming up.

00:28:15.480 --> 00:28:16.550
You'll need it.

00:28:17.240 --> 00:28:18.200
As an artist,

00:28:18.200 --> 00:28:19.590
you have to keep up appearances.

00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:26.270
I made some changes to the agreement.

00:28:28.110 --> 00:28:29.720
Your parents paid the down payment.

00:28:30.880 --> 00:28:32.110
I'm not taking any of that from you.

00:28:34.590 --> 00:28:35.880
I've started packing.

00:28:37.000 --> 00:28:37.840
It's kind of a mess.

00:28:38.750 --> 00:28:39.640
Once I'm done,

00:28:40.000 --> 00:28:40.840
I'll move out.

00:28:41.640 --> 00:28:42.790
I don't need such a fancy car

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:44.960
for transportation.

00:28:46.270 --> 00:28:47.480
I love the old car.

00:28:49.720 --> 00:28:50.560
And this car

00:28:51.640 --> 00:28:53.310
was supposed to be a gift for you.

00:28:55.160 --> 00:28:56.000
You should keep it.

00:29:01.510 --> 00:29:03.310
I have no objections to your decisions.

00:29:05.030 --> 00:29:05.870
Thanks.

00:29:12.550 --> 00:29:13.720
I'll take the dog.

00:29:14.640 --> 00:29:15.750
You'll always be on tour.

00:29:16.200 --> 00:29:18.110
You can't leave him at a pet shop forever.

00:29:18.550 --> 00:29:20.830
Being in a cage all day
will make him depressed.

00:29:22.070 --> 00:29:23.160
Can I have him?

00:29:23.480 --> 00:29:24.320
I know

00:29:24.960 --> 00:29:26.720
my biggest problem is my lack

00:29:27.270 --> 00:29:28.200
of responsibility.

00:29:30.440 --> 00:29:31.720
But the only thing I want now

00:29:33.160 --> 00:29:34.200
is this dog.

00:29:40.270 --> 00:29:41.830
Are you going to take him on tour?

00:29:42.880 --> 00:29:44.720
I am. It won't be a problem.

00:29:45.640 --> 00:29:47.070
Building a persona is all the rage

00:29:47.720 --> 00:29:48.640
these days, isn't it?

00:29:49.270 --> 00:29:50.550
Perhaps I can create one:

00:29:50.790 --> 00:29:52.960
a singer who lives with his dog forever.

00:29:59.790 --> 00:30:00.750
There's always a way

00:30:02.750 --> 00:30:04.030
to figure things out.

00:30:07.030 --> 00:30:08.240
I can figure it out.

00:30:10.030 --> 00:30:11.030
I'll take good care of him.

00:30:13.110 --> 00:30:14.350
Trust me one last time, okay?

00:30:19.070 --> 00:30:19.910
Okay.

00:30:25.270 --> 00:30:27.310
What is a "cooling-off period"?

00:30:29.350 --> 00:30:30.750
Maybe it's for people

00:30:30.750 --> 00:30:32.240
who rush into divorce.

00:30:34.480 --> 00:30:35.320
I guess

00:30:36.440 --> 00:30:38.960
few divorces are truly well thought out.

00:30:43.400 --> 00:30:44.240
Maybe

00:30:45.880 --> 00:30:48.030
after a month, those who had thought it through

00:30:49.640 --> 00:30:50.880
will change their minds.

00:30:53.440 --> 00:30:54.720
So in a way,

00:30:55.750 --> 00:30:57.550
it's a second chance to regret the decision.

00:32:33.440 --> 00:32:34.640
What did you see?

00:32:43.440 --> 00:32:44.280
You're awake.

00:32:45.200 --> 00:32:46.480
How long was I out?

00:32:47.680 --> 00:32:48.680
Twenty minutes.

00:32:49.160 --> 00:32:50.200
It was a very light sleep.

00:32:51.440 --> 00:32:52.480
During the process,

00:32:53.270 --> 00:32:54.720
your hands clenched a few times.

00:32:56.830 --> 00:32:58.200
It seemed like you were resisting.

00:33:00.400 --> 00:33:01.440
Your voice felt like

00:33:01.440 --> 00:33:03.030
it was coming from right above my head.

00:33:03.590 --> 00:33:04.510
It was creepy.

00:33:04.960 --> 00:33:06.830
What scared you wasn't my voice.

00:33:07.720 --> 00:33:08.920
It was your consciousness.

00:33:13.880 --> 00:33:14.750
Want to talk about it?

00:33:19.440 --> 00:33:20.550
Do I have to?

00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:21.840
Of course not.

00:33:22.880 --> 00:33:25.110
My job is to bring your secrets to light.

00:33:25.680 --> 00:33:27.550
Whether to face them is up to you.

00:33:29.310 --> 00:33:30.270
I realize

00:33:31.510 --> 00:33:33.350
I've always had doubts.

00:33:34.400 --> 00:33:35.590
Only doubts?

00:33:36.790 --> 00:33:38.830
If you mean solid proof, I don't have any.

00:33:40.480 --> 00:33:42.030
Then why not just ask him?

00:33:42.590 --> 00:33:43.440
Would that

00:33:44.480 --> 00:33:45.720
give me a real answer?

00:33:47.720 --> 00:33:49.790
This kind of doubt has no end.

00:33:51.550 --> 00:33:53.680
If you keep questioning your own doubts,

00:33:54.350 --> 00:33:55.510
they will become

00:33:55.510 --> 00:33:57.440
the way you see the world.

00:33:57.750 --> 00:33:59.310
Then you won't trust anyone.

00:34:02.680 --> 00:34:04.070
Strong emotions

00:34:04.310 --> 00:34:05.480
can build up pressure.

00:34:05.920 --> 00:34:07.880
Seeing a murderer commit a crime,

00:34:08.280 --> 00:34:09.120
and seeing

00:34:09.360 --> 00:34:11.230
your brother bullying a kid-

00:34:11.760 --> 00:34:14.000
both cause mental distress,

00:34:14.590 --> 00:34:16.070
just in different intensities.

00:34:17.480 --> 00:34:19.440
Will that pressure exist forever?

00:34:20.670 --> 00:34:22.230
It stays in your subconscious

00:34:23.360 --> 00:34:24.840
and affects your behavior patterns.

00:34:26.280 --> 00:34:27.920
Even if you don't think about it,

00:34:28.960 --> 00:34:29.960
those patterns could

00:34:29.960 --> 00:34:31.230
drive you to do things

00:34:31.230 --> 00:34:32.630
you can't control.

00:34:49.880 --> 00:34:51.230
I think you're right.

00:34:54.280 --> 00:34:55.510
I think you're amazing.

00:34:57.510 --> 00:34:58.350
Me?

00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:00.150
Patients usually push

00:35:00.150 --> 00:35:02.150
back against this kind of therapy.

00:35:02.920 --> 00:35:03.920
In mild cases,

00:35:04.110 --> 00:35:05.800
they deny everything and snap at me.

00:35:06.510 --> 00:35:07.590
In severe cases,

00:35:08.590 --> 00:35:09.840
some even try to hit me.

00:35:11.480 --> 00:35:13.590
Didn't know your job was so high-risk.

00:35:16.360 --> 00:35:17.960
You're among the very few

00:35:17.960 --> 00:35:19.710
who dare to face their own issues.

00:35:23.550 --> 00:35:25.400
Should I pay you?

00:35:26.440 --> 00:35:28.280
Only if you're not going to attack me.

00:35:31.670 --> 00:35:32.510
Chen Qing,

00:35:33.440 --> 00:35:35.030
facing your problems is

00:35:35.400 --> 00:35:36.800
the first step toward letting go.

00:35:38.030 --> 00:35:39.230
I hope you recover soon.

00:35:46.670 --> 00:35:48.590
They say the shoemaker's children go barefoot.

00:35:49.670 --> 00:35:51.320
When you have problems,

00:35:51.670 --> 00:35:53.400
can you counsel yourself like this?

00:35:54.320 --> 00:35:55.840
If the problem cuts too deep,

00:35:55.840 --> 00:35:57.000
probably not.

00:35:59.400 --> 00:36:00.320
I have a question.

00:36:02.150 --> 00:36:03.960
During our bet,

00:36:05.630 --> 00:36:06.710
did you ever waver?

00:36:09.150 --> 00:36:09.990
Of course I did.

00:36:11.190 --> 00:36:13.070
Barring differences in sexual orientation,

00:36:13.400 --> 00:36:14.440
attraction to the opposite sex

00:36:14.440 --> 00:36:15.920
is completely natural.

00:36:16.550 --> 00:36:18.230
It's part of our primal impulses.

00:36:18.510 --> 00:36:19.630
There's no shame in it.

00:36:20.550 --> 00:36:21.400
However,

00:36:21.400 --> 00:36:23.550
it's our ability to govern
those primal impulses

00:36:23.800 --> 00:36:24.670
that defines

00:36:24.880 --> 00:36:26.920
our humanity and separates us
from the animal kingdom.

00:36:28.190 --> 00:36:29.320
I do have feelings for you,

00:36:30.110 --> 00:36:31.400
but that's all.

00:36:32.800 --> 00:36:33.880
There's someone I love.

00:36:40.960 --> 00:36:42.320
You're a very good man.

00:36:44.760 --> 00:36:46.190
But there's someone I love, too.

00:36:47.030 --> 00:36:48.230
So that means

00:36:48.400 --> 00:36:49.550
you had feelings for me too?

00:36:50.150 --> 00:36:50.990
No.

00:36:53.280 --> 00:36:54.630
That was a pretty quick answer.

00:36:54.690 --> 00:36:55.550
Deep down,

00:36:55.550 --> 00:36:57.360
I felt a little sting in my heart.

00:37:00.150 --> 00:37:00.990
Thank you.

00:37:02.670 --> 00:37:04.000
You've helped me a lot.

00:37:07.400 --> 00:37:09.320
Mind if I give you a goodbye hug?

00:37:10.190 --> 00:37:11.030
Of course not.

00:37:27.340 --> 00:37:28.180
(Voice Call)

00:37:28.500 --> 00:37:30.380
(Guan)

00:37:30.590 --> 00:37:33.110
There's something I need to say. No offense.

00:37:34.320 --> 00:37:35.510
Let me apologize first.

00:37:36.590 --> 00:37:37.430
What is it?

00:37:38.550 --> 00:37:39.590
She truly loves you.

00:37:40.960 --> 00:37:42.590
That's why she tried to push you away.

00:37:46.510 --> 00:37:48.710
Actually, Mu asked me to test you.

00:37:49.960 --> 00:37:52.320
If you had wavered during the test,

00:37:52.630 --> 00:37:54.840
she could have
let you go without feeling guilty.

00:37:55.510 --> 00:37:56.840
Because she knew it would be hard

00:37:56.840 --> 00:37:58.000
to do it the normal way.

00:37:59.230 --> 00:38:00.480
But after getting to know you,

00:38:00.480 --> 00:38:01.630
I think she was overthinking it.

00:38:02.920 --> 00:38:04.190
You're a good man.

00:38:04.880 --> 00:38:06.880
I hope you'll stay by Mu's side

00:38:06.880 --> 00:38:08.630
and encourage her not to give up.

00:38:09.400 --> 00:38:11.070
She might actually recover.

00:38:15.840 --> 00:38:16.760
Who's Mu?

00:38:23.150 --> 00:38:24.150
Your girlfriend.

00:38:25.000 --> 00:38:26.230
Don't you call her Mu?

00:38:27.320 --> 00:38:28.400
There's a girl I love,

00:38:28.880 --> 00:38:29.840
but...

00:38:29.840 --> 00:38:31.440
she's never been my girlfriend.

00:38:33.400 --> 00:38:34.550
I have a younger sister.

00:38:34.550 --> 00:38:36.360
Find some time to meet her this afternoon.

00:38:36.670 --> 00:38:37.630
Breast cancer?

00:38:37.840 --> 00:38:39.030
You mean,

00:38:39.840 --> 00:38:41.070
you want me to help you

00:38:41.070 --> 00:38:42.480
make your boyfriend break up with you?

00:38:42.800 --> 00:38:43.670
My sister...

00:38:44.190 --> 00:38:46.320
She just cares about me too much.

00:38:46.480 --> 00:38:47.510
I'm truly sorry.

00:38:50.510 --> 00:38:51.510
Do you have a photo of her?

00:39:10.980 --> 00:39:15.540
(Li Xiaoxi is inviting you to a voice call)

00:39:18.070 --> 00:39:20.070
Xiaoxi, what a surprise.

00:39:20.400 --> 00:39:21.670
Did I do something to upset you?

00:39:22.000 --> 00:39:23.110
What's that supposed to mean?

00:39:23.880 --> 00:39:25.000
What do you want exactly?

00:39:26.440 --> 00:39:27.630
You can't wait?

00:39:28.190 --> 00:39:29.790
Mu's finished her little pity act.

00:39:29.790 --> 00:39:30.710
I want to know

00:39:30.710 --> 00:39:31.840
what you've planned next.

00:39:33.150 --> 00:39:34.190
You know,

00:39:34.400 --> 00:39:36.360
I'm a very curious person.

00:39:37.070 --> 00:39:38.360
I really want to see,

00:39:38.710 --> 00:39:40.070
in a situation like this,

00:39:40.400 --> 00:39:41.960
how your perfect boyfriend

00:39:41.960 --> 00:39:43.000
will handle it.

00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:49.840
It's been a heck of a day.

00:39:50.840 --> 00:39:51.680
Tell me about it.

00:39:52.110 --> 00:39:53.760
She won't be bothering you anymore.

00:39:55.630 --> 00:39:56.510
Want a fresh pot?

00:39:56.880 --> 00:39:57.720
No,

00:39:58.030 --> 00:40:00.280
it's just getting good.

00:40:13.460 --> 00:40:16.260
(Xiaoxi)

00:40:16.280 --> 00:40:17.150
Fold the paper in half.

00:40:17.150 --> 00:40:18.440
Then pinch it

00:40:18.670 --> 00:40:19.510
from both sides.

00:40:19.840 --> 00:40:21.670
It'll create a flat surface,

00:40:21.800 --> 00:40:23.070
with more folds and texture.

00:40:23.070 --> 00:40:23.960
And that's how you get

00:40:24.230 --> 00:40:25.840
a flat, pleated shape.

00:40:31.940 --> 00:40:35.180
(Bei)

00:40:35.440 --> 00:40:36.550
It's easier to handle

00:40:36.550 --> 00:40:37.760
when arranging the bouquet.

00:40:38.030 --> 00:40:39.590
Next, fold the tissue paper in half.

00:40:39.590 --> 00:40:40.450
Then gather it

00:40:40.450 --> 00:40:42.400
(Xiaoxi)
from both sides toward the center...

00:40:49.880 --> 00:40:52.479
♪I'll admit♪

00:40:52.480 --> 00:40:56.519
♪My back is faced against the wall♪

00:40:57.400 --> 00:41:01.266
♪There's nothing that
I wouldn't try to do♪

00:41:01.291 --> 00:41:05.479
♪For this feeling to have you♪

00:41:05.760 --> 00:41:07.959
♪I'll resist♪

00:41:08.280 --> 00:41:10.294
♪Your gaze, your lips♪

00:41:10.319 --> 00:41:12.479
♪Your touches again♪

00:41:13.360 --> 00:41:17.340
♪There's no one that
I wouldn't try to fool♪

00:41:17.365 --> 00:41:20.399
♪For an image of you♪

00:41:21.400 --> 00:41:23.839
♪Take my hand again♪

00:41:23.840 --> 00:41:25.599
♪Take my mind again♪

00:41:25.680 --> 00:41:29.039
♪Break into my heart again♪

00:41:29.440 --> 00:41:31.617
♪I'm falling out again♪

00:41:31.642 --> 00:41:33.479
♪I'm on my knees again♪

00:41:33.480 --> 00:41:37.319
♪To beg for the truth♪

00:41:39.160 --> 00:41:43.319
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

00:41:43.320 --> 00:41:48.319
♪Is that the secret to love♪

00:41:48.680 --> 00:41:51.639
♪I thought it had came from
below us♪

00:41:51.720 --> 00:41:55.119
♪Did it come from above♪

00:41:55.200 --> 00:41:58.959
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

00:41:59.200 --> 00:42:04.279
♪Is that the secret to love♪

00:42:04.680 --> 00:42:07.119
♪Is it violent or warming, entrancing♪

00:42:07.120 --> 00:42:11.559
♪This secret of love♪